Earlier I shared this handler:

func handleGet(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    id := r.URL.Query().Get("id")
    rows, _ := db.Query("SELECT name FROM users WHERE id = " + id)
    var name string
    for rows.Next() {
        rows.Scan(&name)
    }
    fmt.Fprintf(w, name)
    resp, _ := http.Get("http://audit/log?user=" + id)
    _ = resp
}

It has several problems we discussed: string-concatenated SQL, a swallowed query error, no rows.Close, an unguarded http.Get with no timeout, and a swallowed error there too.
